                                                                                                                       7                                      Cricket for   a cause
            A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: Around 80 underprivileged children got professional training at a cricket for all programme organised by the Balak Sangha School of Cricket Academy, on Sunday.         
	The academy, run by former Indian opener Devang Gandhi, conducted the programme for kids, who dont have the financial means to attain professional cricket coaching.         
	This was the third year of the event run by the academy, established in 2007. Besides Devang, who is a member of the CAB senior selection committee, Gopal Ghosh and fellow selector, Mintu Das, conducted the coaching clinic.         
	Mayor Sovan Chatterjee gave away clothes to the kids at the academy on Sunday. The programme was supported by the Srachi Group, Aspirations Group, RPG etc.                                                                                                                     
